<!-- ABOUT PANDEMICS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>About Pandemics</h2>
  <p>
    A pandemic occurs when a new infectious disease spreads rapidly across countries and continents.
    Examples include COVID-19, H1N1, and past outbreaks like SARS and Spanish Flu.
  </p>
  <p>
    Pandemics disrupt daily life, health systems, education, travel, and economy.
  </p>
</article>

<!-- TRANSMISSION -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>How Diseases Spread</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Respiratory droplets (coughing, sneezing).</li>
    <li>Close contact with infected people.</li>
    <li>Touching contaminated surfaces.</li>
    <li>Airborne particles in crowded or closed spaces.</li>
    <li>Through hands touching eyes, nose, mouth.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- SYMPTOMS -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Common Symptoms</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Fever & cough</li>
    <li>Breathing difficulty</li>
    <li>Fatigue & body pain</li>
    <li>Loss of smell or taste (COVID-19)</li>
    <li>Headache, sore throat</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<!-- PREVENTION -->
<article class="content-card">
  <h2>Prevention & Safety Measures</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Wear masks in crowded places.</li>
    <li>Wash hands with soap for 20 seconds.</li>
    <li>Use sanitizer (min. 60% alcohol).</li>
    <li>Maintain physical distancing.</li>
    <li>Avoid touching face unnecessarily.</li>
    <li>Ensure proper ventilation indoors.</li>
    <li>Cover mouth while coughing/sneezing.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

